  "In a two-way table, 30 students play sports and 20 do not. Of those who play sports, 18 are male. How many females play sports?": "",
  "20": "",
  "18": "",
  "12": "",
  "10": "",
  "If 30 students play sports and 18 are male, then 30 - 18 = 12 females play sports.": "",
  "A two-way table shows: Cat owners = 45, Dog owners = 55, total surveyed = 100. These numbers appear in the bottom row. What are these values called?": "",
  "Relative frequencies": "",
  "Conditional frequencies": "",
  "Marginal frequencies": "",
  "Joint frequencies": "",
