  "A pet store tracks pet adoptions by type (Cat, Dog) and adopter age group (Under 30, 30-50, Over 50). Results: Under 30 cats=25, Under 30 dogs=40, 30-50 cats=30, 30-50 dogs=35, Over 50 cats=45, Over 50 dogs=25. A marketing manager says cats are more popular overall. Is this correct?": "",
